{"type":"message","id":"5c7f1832","parentId":"da7cef35","timestamp":"2026-04-14T15:32:55.352Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking about a safety concern - if I would delete important files without asking. This is a reasonable question about my operating procedures. Looking at SOUL.md and AGENTS.md, there are safety rules:\n\n1. AGENTS.md has \"Red Lines\" - \"Don't exfiltrate private data. Ever.\" and \"Don't run destructive commands without asking.\" and \"`trash` > `rm` (recoverable beats gone forever)\" and \"When in doubt, ask.\"\n\n2. SOUL.md has absolute prohibitions and risk level definitions.\n\nFor HIGH risk operations (like destructive commands), SOUL.md says I need to prepend `[!WARNING]` and provide rollback steps. For CRITICAL operations (like `rm -rf /`), the system layer hard-blocks.\n \nSo the framework already has built-in safeguards - I'm not just barreling forward with destructive actions. For HIGH risk, I warn first and provide rollback options. For CRITICAL, the system itself blocks the operation before it ever reaches me. The \"do it first\" philosophy really just means I don't pad responses with unnecessary disclaimers on straightforward tasks.","thinkingSignature":"1f1e1f365c1a9cc631f45dbdebaee65c6e336d932ce8e557a0b758e34215c920"},{"type":"text","text":"不会。SOUL.md 里我有一条\"绝对禁令\"——危险操作（HIGH风险及以上）必须前置 `[!WARNING]` 并提供回滚方案，CRITICAL 直接系统层硬拦截。\n\n\"先做了再说\"指的是信息查询、代码生成、文件分析这类无副作用的任务。有破坏性的操作该拦还是拦。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":54,"output":297,"cacheRead":23064,"cacheWrite":114,"totalTokens":23529,"cost":{"input":0.0000162,"output":0.0003564,"cacheRead":0.00138384,"cacheWrite":0.00004275,"total":0.00179919}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776180762485,"responseId":"062d91191ca18b6426ba88fd59293bc6"}}
