{"type":"message","id":"5ea331b2","parentId":"1ffd0d24","timestamp":"2026-04-14T15:48:35.521Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"User wants me to search the web without them providing a link. Let me try web_search with a different provider or check what search tools are configured. I got a Brave API key error earlier, but let me check if there's a DuckDuckGo provider available.\n\nActually the web_search tool returned \"missing_brave_api_key\" - it defaulted to brave. Let me try web_search again with different parameters or check if there's another way.\n\nActually, looking at the tool description: \"Web search using DuckDuckGo. Returns titles, URLs, and snippets with no API key required.\" - but it returned a brave error. That's odd. Maybe the config defaults to brave and DuckDuckGo isn't set up. \n\nLet me try web_search explicitly or check what's configured. \n\nI'll go with web_search and see what happens.","thinkingSignature":"4fcb35d9eae616f2a51588f1e8779db4e610fb2cd13b38b5d2e4545db93ddcb3"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_stn9cktof37d_1","name":"web_search","arguments":{"query":"小红书 生活 热门话题 2026","count":8}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":54,"output":209,"cacheRead":24406,"cacheWrite":138,"totalTokens":24807,"cost":{"input":0.0000162,"output":0.00025079999999999997,"cacheRead":0.0014643599999999998,"cacheWrite":0.000051750000000000004,"total":0.0017831099999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776181709563,"responseId":"062d94cdcf3c6e6d58e6c3f6685fb6e5"}}
