{"type":"message","id":"4a81655d","parentId":"10a6e1f0","timestamp":"2026-04-14T15:50:51.724Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Tue 2026-04-14 23:50 GMT+8] 看看有没有风险，是不是恶意工具，深入分析思考一下"}],"timestamp":1776181851715}}
{"type":"message","id":"d19b1615","parentId":"4a81655d","timestamp":"2026-04-14T15:51:19.645Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to deeply analyze whether Agent-Reach is safe or malicious. Let me think about this carefully.\n\nKey things to analyze:\n1. What the tool does (accesses platforms like 小红书, Twitter, Reddit etc.)\n2. The code/source (open source MIT license)\n3. The author (Panniantong - who is this?)\n4. The upstream tools it relies on (xhs-cli, twitter-cli, etc.)\n5. Security implications (Cookie handling, data privacy)\n6. Whether it could be malicious\n\nLet me think through this systematically:\n\n**What it does:**\n- Installs various CLI tools that interact with social media platforms\n- Uses cookies for authentication to Twitter, 小红书, Reddit\n- Stores credentials locally in ~/.agent-reach/config.yaml\n\n\n- Registers SKILL.md files in the agent's skills directory\n\n**Potential risks:**\n1. Cookie theft - the tool asks for cookies from Twitter/小红书/Reddit. Cookies = full login access. If the tool is malicious, it could steal cookies.\n2. SKILL.md injection - it registers skill files that tell the agent to run certain commands. Could those be malicious?\n3. Upstream tool integrity - it installs pip packages from PyPI\n4. The tool requires exec permissions in OpenClaw (shell command execution)\n\n**Mitigating factors:**\n1. MIT license - open source, code can be reviewed\n2. The README explicitly warns about account bans and recommends using small accounts\n3. It uses official CLI tools (gh CLI, yt-dlp, etc.)\n4. Cookie data stays local according to the README\n\n**My assessment:**\n- I can't directly inspect the code since I don't have the repository cloned\n- The README contains security warnings and explains its design philosophy clearly\n- I should examine the actual source code to give a more definitive answer\n- This appears to be a legitimate tool that accesses social media platforms through official CLI interfaces, though it does carry inherent risks with credential handling\n- The main concerns are account suspension from platform detection and the potential for credential exposure if the tool or its dependencies are compromised\n- From an OpenClaw security angle, I'm evaluating the attack surface: shell execution with pip installation, cookie authentication to external services, and what agent-reach doctor commands actually do\n- This falls into a higher risk category because it involves third-party tools I can't fully vet, credential handling, and potentially violating platform terms of service\n- My recommendation would be to avoid using this in production or with sensitive accounts\n- Now I need to look at the actual source code to complete my assessment","thinkingSignature":"5b03d7e456f57ec7099363ac1d6cef489465c14addbbc55db5a20653276a0bd7"},{"type":"text","text":"<thinking>\n### 1. 需求拆解\n用户要我深入分析 Agent-Reach 是否有风险、是否为恶意工具。需要从代码、架构、依赖、隐私、安全模型多角度审视。\n\n### 2. 方案推演\n分析路径：\n1. 拉源码审查核心文件（install.py、channels/）\n2. 看上游依赖包（xhs-cli、twitter-cli）在 PyPI 上的信息\n3. 分析它实际跑什么命令\n4. 评估 Cookie 处理的安全性\n5. SKILL.md 注册机制有没有注入风险\n6. 对比 OpenClaw 的安全边界\n\n### 3. 自我质疑\n我之前只读了 README，没看源码。README 写得好不代表代码没问题。MIT license 开源项目也可能恶意——PyPI 上有恶意包钓鱼的历史。需要实际看代码。\n\n### 4. 最终决策\n先抓源码核心文件审查，再给出结论。\n</thinking>\n\n读 README 不够，得看源码。抓核心文件审查：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_kh4fgyi1ac92_1","name":"web_fetch","arguments":{"url":"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Panniantong/agent-reach/main/install.py","maxChars":10000}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_kh4fgyi1ac92_2","name":"web_fetch","arguments":{"url":"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Panniantong/agent-reach/main/agent_reach/__init__.py","maxChars":10000}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_kh4fgyi1ac92_3","name":"web_fetch","arguments":{"url":"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Panniantong/agent-reach/main/channels/xiaohongshu.py","maxChars":5000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":54,"output":897,"cacheRead":24949,"cacheWrite":9189,"totalTokens":35089,"cost":{"input":0.0000162,"output":0.0010764,"cacheRead":0.0014969399999999998,"cacheWrite":0.003445875,"total":0.006035415}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776181851731,"responseId":"062d955b4c956ead97f4175014fe0f2c"}}
