{"type":"message","id":"1978080f","parentId":"18e9266f","timestamp":"2026-04-14T16:01:03.722Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No proxy environment variables are set. The web_fetch works because it uses some internal proxy mechanism, but the shell commands don't have that.\n\nLet me think differently. The web_fetch tool works. Can I use it to download the tarball content and then write it to a file? web_fetch can fetch content, but it's text-focused. Let me see if I can use the GitHub API via web_fetch to get the tarball URL and then...\n\nActually, the GitHub API works via web_fetch (`https://api.github.com/repos/...` returned JSON). The issue is that the tarball download URL (`https://api.github.com/repos/Panniantong/agent-reach/tarball/main`) redirected to `https://codeload.github.com/...` which then timed out.\n \nI'm hitting a wall with web_fetch—it can retrieve the tarball but there's no way to persist it to disk. The exec commands might work if I configure git to use a proxy, but without knowing the proxy address that web_fetch relies on, I'm stuck. Let me try checking if there's a system-wide proxy configuration I can leverage.","thinkingSignature":"44c472eb46cfb6bc8b75a8a3b3a6c42942b5cd9852cf48779fda1b8994849d54"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_uat7ydol8jwu_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"git config --global --list 2>/dev/null; git config --global http.proxy 2>/dev/null; git config --global https.proxy 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":38933,"output":290,"cacheRead":20080,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":59303,"cost":{"input":0.0116799,"output":0.000348,"cacheRead":0.0012047999999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0132327}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776182455121,"responseId":"062d97b6af453186933bef088ff8a92f"}}
