{"type":"message","id":"2f80ade7","parentId":"d764ebcf","timestamp":"2026-04-14T16:01:10.099Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! There's a git config that rewrites GitHub URLs to use SSH instead of HTTPS. That's interesting. Let me check if `gh` CLI is configured and if I can use it to fetch the tarball.\n\nActually wait - the git config shows `url.https://github.com/.insteadof=ssh://git@github.com/` which means it's converting SSH URLs to HTTPS. But more importantly, there's a `credential.helper=!/usr/bin/gh auth git-credential` which means it's using the GitHub CLI for authentication.\n\nLet me try using `gh api` to download the tarball since gh is configured.","thinkingSignature":"e774b0f9ab3ed75a2be06091122454b1f220c05ae451131b66de496f6f7684bb"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_tzfytuov75lj_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"gh api repos/Panniantong/agent-reach/tarball/main -s -o /tmp/agent-reach.tar.gz 2>&1; ls -la /tmp/agent-reach.tar.gz 2>&1","timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":39311,"output":209,"cacheRead":20080,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":59600,"cost":{"input":0.0117933,"output":0.00025079999999999997,"cacheRead":0.0012047999999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.013248900000000001}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776182463811,"responseId":"062d97bfa5e72bba044c6afe85f8cfc7"}}
