{"type":"message","id":"4a8193c2","parentId":"4cb650b3","timestamp":"2026-04-14T16:04:02.710Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The xhs binary is not there, only python and python3. This means the installation was incomplete. The uv tool install started downloading but got killed before completing.\n\nThe problem is that installing xhs-cli requires downloading playwright (44MB!) which keeps getting killed. \n\nLet me think about alternative approaches:\n1. Maybe I can install a lighter version without playwright\n2. Maybe I can use a different tool that does the same thing\n3. Maybe I should ask the user to install it locally\n\nActually, let me look at what the xiaohongshu-cli actually requires and if there's a way to install it without playwright (which is the heavy dependency).\n\nLooking at the PyPI page, the features include \"Anti-detection\" with \"playwright\" mentioned. But maybe there's a way to install it without the heavy browser automation parts.\n\n\nI should check the xhs-cli source code directly to understand what's actually required versus what's optional for the installation.","thinkingSignature":"9042b194cf331193814e0cf3474944d321a24659061d6728fb735d0962ce0e26"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_tekfzk2xo06g_1","name":"web_fetch","arguments":{"url":"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/jackwener/xiaohongshu-cli/main/pyproject.toml","maxChars":5000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":45281,"output":251,"cacheRead":20080,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65612,"cost":{"input":0.013584299999999999,"output":0.0003012,"cacheRead":0.0012047999999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.015090299999999997}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776182634341,"responseId":"062d986a3dcf22794301d594ec43d10b"}}
