{"type":"message","id":"4d7adca9","parentId":"28da01fd","timestamp":"2026-04-14T16:04:41.784Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So `xhs` is a Python SDK - `XhsClient`. It's not a CLI tool. To use it, I'd need to write Python code that uses the SDK. \n\nThis isn't a good fit for an AI agent that mostly uses shell commands. The `xiaohongshu-cli` (which provides the `xhs` CLI command) is what we need, but it keeps failing to install because of the large playwright download.\n\nLet me think about what else I can try:\n1. Can I install playwright separately and then install xhs-cli without the playwright part?\n2. Is there a way to get a pre-built binary?3. Can I manually download just the CLI part?\n\nActually, let me try to install just the `xhs` CLI package from a different source, or check if there's a way to use the SDK as a CLI through a helper script.Or maybe I should give up on xhs-cli and try a completely different approach - like using the xiaohongshu web directly through some other method.Let me actually check if there's a way to use the xhs SDK from the command line. Maybe it has an entry point I don't know about.","thinkingSignature":"7104208d7068ecccf57726847fc0358b874e456bd6b7e702066899b9d6aeb2bd"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_mp847tri1otz_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"from xhs import XhsClient; help(XhsClient)\" 2>&1 | head -40","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":46776,"output":303,"cacheRead":20080,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":67159,"cost":{"input":0.0140328,"output":0.0003636,"cacheRead":0.0012047999999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.015601199999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776182673352,"responseId":"062d9891f4d0e72b5dbcbc1b5f9dbab2"}}
