{"type":"message","id":"bd314029","parentId":"7f7bab4e","timestamp":"2026-04-14T16:04:49.034Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `xhs` SDK is quite comprehensive - it has `get_note`, `search_note`, `get_user`, `get_home_feed`, etc. It's a proper SDK. But it's not a CLI - there's no command to just run `xhs search \"keyword\"`.\n\nI could write a Python script that uses this SDK to perform the desired operations. That would be a reasonable approach. The SDK requires a cookie to be set, so we'd still need the user to provide their Xiaohongshu cookie.\n\nLet me write a simple Python script that uses the xhs SDK. First, let me understand the search functionality.","thinkingSignature":"3ae09f598f10d6f13ff4fce5cebb881b8b64cbd8a02a7abd0184d140b4648181"},{"type":"text","text":"`xhs` 是 SDK 不是 CLI，但能用。写个脚本接上：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_s92hmv66qgjm_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"from xhs import XhsClient; c = XhsClient(); print([m for m in dir(c) if not m.startswith('_')])\" 2>&1","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":47486,"output":219,"cacheRead":20080,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":67785,"cost":{"input":0.0142458,"output":0.0002628,"cacheRead":0.0012047999999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0157134}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776182682001,"responseId":"062d989ae525619d46979fe1ba2eaa09"}}
