{"type":"message","id":"d298b080","parentId":"11a236ee","timestamp":"2026-04-14T16:04:55.401Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The xhs SDK has a bug with the `|=` operator on Python 3.8 (dict |= was introduced in Python 3.9). This is a compatibility issue. The SDK requires Python 3.9+ but we're on Python 3.8.\n\nSo we have multiple problems:\n1. Python 3.8 doesn't support `|=` for dicts (introduced in 3.9)\n2. The xhs SDK is not compatible with Python 3.8\n\nLet me check if there's a way to install a newer Python or work around this.Actually, let me try using `uv run` with a newer Python version, since uv seems to have its own Python installations.","thinkingSignature":"6872acfe820ca882abe44db8d68fb236d5d01d397ad6c967fa76dc6e649e9e35"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_21ims6m0iipf_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"uv run python --version 2>&1; uv run python -c \"import sys; print(sys.version)\" 2>&1","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":47909,"output":206,"cacheRead":20080,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":68195,"cost":{"input":0.014372699999999999,"output":0.0002472,"cacheRead":0.0012047999999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.015824699999999997}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776182689252,"responseId":"062d98a1e3419f68da1e016348b53b76"}}
