{"type":"message","id":"e879a9b9","parentId":"82581f87","timestamp":"2026-04-14T16:33:23.590Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see a potential issue here: `self.cookie = cookie` at line 124 sets the cookie via the setter. The setter calls `update_session_cookies_from_cookie(self.__session, cookie)`. Since cookie is None (no cookie passed), and we already patched `update_session_cookies_from_cookie`, it would use the default cookie values.\n\nBut wait - there's another issue. The `__init__` signature:\n```python\ndef __init__(self, cookie=None, user_agent=None, timeout=10, proxies=None, sign=None):\n```\n\nAnd later:\n```python\nself.external_sign = sign\n```\n\nIf the user passes `sign=None` (the default), then `self.external_sign = sign` sets it to None! The parameter name `sign` shadows the imported `sign` function. \n\nActually, that's not it - we're not passing any arguments, so `sign` defaults to None and overwrites `self.external_sign`. But the imported `sign` is available in the module scope. The real problem is that when we instantiate `XhsClient()` without arguments, the `sign` parameter gets set to None, which then gets assigned to `self.external_sign` instead of using the imported function.\n\nThe solution is to check if `sign` is None and use the imported `sign` function from the module scope instead. The cleanest fix is to add a default value of None to the parameter, then assign `self.external_sign = sign if sign is not None else sign` - but that's circular. The real fix is to rename the parameter to something like `custom_sign` to avoid shadowing the imported function altogether. But I'm also wondering if there's something about how Python 3.8 handles default arguments that I'm missing here. The issue is that when `sign=None` is passed explicitly, it shadows the imported `sign` function. The solution is to default to `None` and then use the imported `sign` if no custom function is provided—something like `self.external_sign = sign if sign is not None else help.sign`. Let me just patch the __init__ to fix this.","thinkingSignature":"48e6079ae411b44f2654bc9804c29be6334ebcb083c6ea8391ad80ade710d7b1"},{"type":"text","text":"找到根本问题了——`__init__` 的参数名 `sign=None` 覆盖了导入的 `sign` 函数，导致 `self.external_sign = None`。修一下：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_n0q3iiaeeikf_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '93,125p' /home/ai/.local/lib/python3.8/site-packages/xhs/core.py","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":57144,"output":529,"cacheRead":20080,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":77753,"cost":{"input":0.0171432,"output":0.0006347999999999999,"cacheRead":0.0012047999999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0189828}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776184387460,"responseId":"062d9f432f154958e484bf5770f167e0"}}
{"type":"message","id":"c52909c8","parentId":"e879a9b9","timestamp":"2026-04-14T16:33:23.698Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_n0q3iiaeeikf_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"class XhsClient:\n    def __init__(\n            self, cookie=None, user_agent=None, timeout=10, proxies=None, sign=None\n    ):\n        \"\"\"constructor\"\"\"\n        self.proxies = proxies\n        self.__session: requests.Session = requests.session()\n        self.timeout = timeout\n        self.external_sign = sign\n        self._host = \"https://edith.xiaohongshu.com\"\n        self._creator_host = \"https://creator.xiaohongshu.com\"\n        self.home = \"https://www.xiaohongshu.com\"\n        self.user_agent = user_agent or (\n            \"Mozilla/5.0 \"\n            \"(Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) \"\n            \"AppleWebKit/537.36 \"\n            \"(KHTML, like Gecko) \"\n            \"Chrome/111.0.0.0 Safari/537.36\"\n        )\n        self.__session.headers = {\n            \"user-agent\": self.user_agent,\n            \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\",\n        }\n        self.cookie = cookie\n\n    @property\n    def cookie(self):\n        return cookie_jar_to_cookie_str(self.__session.cookies)\n\n    @cookie.setter\n    def cookie(self, cookie: str):\n        update_session_cookies_from_cookie(self.__session, cookie)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":68,"aggregated":"class XhsClient:\n    def __init__(\n            self, cookie=None, user_agent=None, timeout=10, proxies=None, sign=None\n    ):\n        \"\"\"constructor\"\"\"\n        self.proxies = proxies\n        self.__session: requests.Session = requests.session()\n        self.timeout = timeout\n        self.external_sign = sign\n        self._host = \"https://edith.xiaohongshu.com\"\n        self._creator_host = \"https://creator.xiaohongshu.com\"\n        self.home = \"https://www.xiaohongshu.com\"\n        self.user_agent = user_agent or