{"type":"message","id":"5a112924","parentId":"d78ebfec","timestamp":"2026-04-14T16:34:00.463Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, I also need to check what `external_sign` returns. Looking at `_pre_headers`:\n\n```python\nself.__session.headers.update(\n    self.external_sign(\n        url,\n        data,\n        a1=self.cookie_dict.get(\"a1\"),\n        web_session=self.cookie_dict.get(\"web_session\", \"\"),\n    )\n)\n```\n\nSo `external_sign` should return a dict that will be used to update the session headers. The `sign` function from `xhs.help` returns `{\"x-s\": ..., \"x-t\": ..., \"x-s-common\": ...}`. So my wrapper needs to return the same format.\n\nLet me fix the wrapper.","thinkingSignature":"1db8f40d89c46b5e20c5b68095cd05146a04584877cea05a4bc4755488a4282e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5utho6c3uwia_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'EOF'\ncontent = open('/home/ai/.local/lib/python3.8/site-packages/xhs/core.py').read()\n\nold = \"\"\"        from xhs.help import sign as _sign\n        if sign is not None:\n            self.external_sign = sign\n        else:\n            def _wrapper(uri, data=None, **kw):\n                return _sign(uri, data, a1=kw.get('a1',''))\n            self.external_sign = _wrapper\n\"\"\"\nnew = \"\"\"        from xhs.help import sign as _sign\n        if sign is not None:\n            self.external_sign = sign\n        else:\n            def _wrapper(uri, data=None, **kw):\n                return _sign(uri, data, a1=kw.get('a1',''))\n            self.external_sign = _wrapper\n\"\"\"\nif old in content:\n    content = content.replace(old, new)\n    open('/home/ai/.local/lib/python3.8/site-packages/xhs/core.py', 'w').write(content)\n    print('ok')\nelse:\n    print('not found, checking current state')\n    idx = content.find('from xhs.help import sign as _sign')\n    print(repr(content[idx:idx+300]))\nEOF\n","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provi