{"type":"message","id":"7c9c9977","parentId":"d75d56c8","timestamp":"2026-04-14T16:34:07.601Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Actually wait, I realize there's a problem with my approach. The `sign` function returns a dict with `x-s`, `x-t`, `x-s-common`. And the code in `_pre_headers` does:\n\n```python\nself.__session.headers.update(self.external_sign(...))\n```\n\nSo the return value of `external_sign` should be a dict that can be used to update headers. My `_wrapper` returns `_sign(uri, data, a1=kw.get('a1',''))` which should return the same dict format. This should work.\n\nBut actually wait - looking at the `sign` function signature: `(uri, data=None, ctime=None, a1='', b1='')` - it accepts `a1` as a positional/keyword argument. \n\nSo `_sign(uri, data, a1=kw.get('a1',''))` should work. Let me test it.","thinkingSignature":"6a3aa8da8d90cacbb2beb844cd2b7bf4feefb601fff0207ec6dd22c65be87361"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_24pe2aabdsnk_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'EOF'\nimport sys\nsys.path.insert(0, '/home/ai/.local/lib/python3.8/site-packages')\n\nfrom xhs import XhsClient\nc = XhsClient()\n\ntry:\n    result = c.get_note_by_keyword(\"咖啡\", page=1, page_size=3)\n    print(\"搜索成功!\")\n    import json\n    print(json.dumps(result, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False)[:1000])\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print(f\"错误: {type(e).__name__}: {e}\")\nEOF\n","timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":59770,"output":339,"cacheRead":20080,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":80189,"cost":{"input":0.017931,"output":0.00040679999999999997,"cacheRead":0.0012047999999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.019542599999999997}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776184440623,"responseId":"062d9f78d0c6836c5520d5b928138e74"}}
