{"type":"message","id":"32109b29","parentId":"f87e173f","timestamp":"2026-04-14T16:43:20.119Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The API returned error code 300011 with message \"当前账号存在异常，请切换账号后重试\" (current account has anomalies, please switch account and retry). This is a server-side detection - Xiaohongshu detected that the account is being accessed programmatically from a different IP/location than usual.\n\nThe cookie works (the API accepted it and returned a specific error message rather than \"no login\"), but the server is blocking the request due to unusual activity detection.\n\nThis is the same as the xhs-cli behavior - the server detected the request came from a different location than where the user normally browses from. The account itself might be fine but the access pattern triggered a security check.\n \nIP geolocation mismatch is likely the culprit - the cookie originates from one location but my server's IP is elsewhere. I should ask the user if they can provide a screenshot of what they're seeing on the Xiaohongshu web interface when they log in, or whether they're able to access it normally through a browser on their current network.","thinkingSignature":"310b87adf26aa1656a4e9f967e1b7e23547f84b70af36eb5de30e29f5447f42c"},{"type":"text","text":"API 连通了（Cookie 有效），但返回 `300011 当前账号存在异常` —— 小红书检测到账号从**不同 IP** 访问，触发了风控。\n\n你的 IP 位置和 Cookie 生成时的 IP 不一致，账号被暂时锁了。\n\n你小红书网页版能正常打开吗？在浏览器里搜东西看视频都正常吗？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":64755,"output":290,"cacheRead":20080,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":85125,"cost":{"input":0.0194265,"output":0.000348,"cacheRead":0.0012047999999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0209793}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776184989186,"responseId":"062da19c1015ed71d057ba7dd72d0145"}}
