{"type":"message","id":"aa38ee41","parentId":"655cc267","timestamp":"2026-04-14T16:44:38.486Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user says they were logged out. This confirms the cookie is invalid/expired. The IP-based blocking is also a factor.\n\nOK, so the cookie from this user's computer won't work because:\n1. The cookie may have been invalidated (logged out)\n2. Even if valid, the IP mismatch would trigger security blocks\n\nFor the xhs SDK to work, we'd need:\n- A cookie from the current session (not logged out)\n- Either the same IP, or a proxy\n\nThe user seems frustrated. Let me think about what to say.\n\nActually - if the user's browser is logged out (they said \"登录被下了\"), then the cookie they gave me was already invalid/expired when they gave it. \n\nThat's why it didn't work. The real issue is they're logged out and we'd need a fresh cookie, plus there's the IP blocking problem. I'm thinking maybe we shouldn't use their main account at all - if we suggest creating a separate test account, it would sidestep both the security concerns and the IP mismatch issue entirely.","thinkingSignature":"d32a7f96f43cc432e3fa186710346002e3207a8199394e2eaa12aae68969b3b9"},{"type":"text","text":"对，Cookie 已经失效了，而且即使用有效 Cookie，这个沙盒的 IP 和你本地不一样，小红书也会拦。\n\n两个思路：\n\n**1. 用代理**（解决 IP 问题）：\n你如果有代理，把代理地址给我，我走你的代理出去就能用同一个 IP。\n\n**2. 不用 Cookie，用 Playwright**（解决登录问题）：\nPlaywright 可以直接打开浏览器用你本地 Chrome 的已登录状态，自动绕过 IP 检测。你本地 Chrome 登录着的话，Playwright 可以读到同样的 Cookie，而且用的是你本地的 IP。\n\n要我试试方案 2 吗？在你的 Windows 机器上跑一个脚本，自动用你本地的 Chrome 扫码登录拿 Cookie。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":54,"output":353,"cacheRead":82625,"cacheWrite":1813,"totalTokens":84845,"cost":{"input":0.0000162,"output":0.0004236,"cacheRead":0.004957499999999999,"cacheWrite":0.000679875,"total":0.006077174999999999}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776185064459,"responseId":"062da1e8b5919244dd0935b5d0a30fab"}}
