{"type":"message","id":"e88c9553","parentId":"84ebf4cf","timestamp":"2026-04-14T16:47:54.624Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking if I can do workflow automation if I can't even crawl Xiaohongshu. They're questioning my value proposition more broadly.\n\nLet me be clear and honest: the Xiaohongshu issue is a network/IP limitation specific to this sandbox environment. It doesn't mean I can't do workflow automation generally. \n\nWorkflow automation would involve things like:\n- File processing\n- API calls to services that ARE accessible\n- Git operations\n- Code execution\n- Data transformation\n- Task orchestration within the sandbox or with accessible services\n\nI should be direct - this sandbox can't access Xiaohongshu but that doesn't make all workflows impossible. I can still do plenty of useful work.","thinkingSignature":"93ea9b8dfec53f4c62f5640149d38525ac6997c993d56b48ff6822f5a88f573a"},{"type":"text","text":"那是两码事。小红书爬不了是因为**沙盒 IP 被封**，不是工具能力问题。\n\n工作流我照常能跑——只要不涉及这个沙盒出不去的服务：\n\n- 读文件、写代码、执行脚本\n- Git 操作（GitHub 走不通，但 gitee 或自建 gitlab 可以）\n- 搜网页（能通的那些）\n- 调 API（PyPI、微博热搜、V2EX、一些公开 API 都能通）\n- 树莓派/服务器运维操作\n\n你现在有什么想自动化的活？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":258,"cacheRead":84981,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":85239,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0.0003096,"cacheRead":0.005098859999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0054084599999999995}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776185263609,"responseId":"062da2aff82667be305200aa30a628e7"}}
